ÔªøTony‚Äôs Date-me Doc
(Last updated: 15 Nov 2025)


N MY UNDERGRADUATE YEARS, I was very focused on my studies.  So when my parents found out after graduation that I had departed from my studies and become interested in solving the world‚Äôs problems, they were surprised and worried that I wouldn‚Äôt be able to find a proper job.  They asked ‚Äúwhy don‚Äôt you become a politician?  We can support your further studies.‚Äù  I responded that while it is an option, there is one vocation with a greater potential to do good, and that is the philosopher.  I hope that by perpetually learning, understanding perspectives, and experiencing all that the world has to offer, I can philosophise with enough acuity to help guide humanity through these turbulent times and contribute to our roadmap for the future.    
About me  
* I am a 25-year-old 175cm-tall man.
* I work as an online tutor, an occupation bestowed upon me by my wanderlust.  Even though I currently live in Melbourne, I could be anywhere, anytime.
* I am agnostic and liberal-leaning.  I don‚Äôt drink or smoke.  I neither have nor want children.
Core values
I am a positive, lively, and happy person.  Life is inherently beautiful, and the world is my playground.  I think most people who meet me would say I have a fun, bubbly character.  I loathe to offend others, though I feel disingenuous telling white lies, so I have become quite adept at telling ‚Äúwhite truths‚Äù.
I am extremely curious.  One of my long-term goals is to ‚Äúclimb the mountain of knowledge‚Äù.  This knowledge includes reading undergraduate textbooks on every major university discipline, but equally includes picking up skills and experiences, travelling the natural and cultural world, and so on.  A Chinese proverb tells me ‚Äúread ten thousand books and journey ten thousand miles‚Äù.  Of course, I realise that life is too short to accomplish this goal, but the process matters more to me than the destination.  Besides, the mountain of knowledge has no summit!
I am independent and free-spirited.  I don‚Äôt like relying on others, and rarely ask others for favours.  Despite being a bit of a people-pleaser, I am highly resistant to peer-pressure, and do not mind being perceived as quirky.  In thought, I am naturally skeptical and like to come to my own conclusions.
I have many ideas and perspectives.  I love exploring the intangible world through conversation, whether that leans objective (such as STEM, history, society, politics, ...) or subjective (such as life, relationships, experiences, identity, ...).  If I think an opinion is one-sided, I feel an urge to defend other perspectives, as ‚Äúa wise man proportions his belief to the evidence‚Äù.  Because of this, I can play a mighty devil‚Äôs advocate, though I realise it is seldom called for.
I am highly greed-avoidant.  I believe that it is possible to live a happy and fulfilling life on a modest amount of money, so I am suspicious of rich people who earn more than they can ever spend.  I would rather do meaningful work voluntarily (and I do) than be paid well to do a bullshit job.  The rich and the poor are both preoccupied with money at the expense of happiness, so I intend to be neither.


‚ÄúTony will no doubt be one of the most interesting people you‚Äôll ever meet. [...] Tony is also incredibly warm and brings a very positive energy to any group activity.‚Äù
      ‚Äî Alan, friend of two years
About you
It is difficult to qualify what one finds attractive.  For me, sharing core values is a good start.  In terms of character, I generally find myself attracted to quieter people who feel deeply, care unabashedly, and whose smile and laughter bring joy to the world.  Having agency and a strong work ethic is also a big plus.  Many of the qualities I am attracted to are shared by affectionate cats, and I confess I absolutely adore cats and it seems they generally like me back!
About us
I believe that the happiest relationships are those where the partners are already happy coming into the relationship.  The most uplifting relationships are those where each partner‚Äôs strengths inspire the other to grow.  The most loving relationships are those built upon a deep friendship and a genuine respect for each other.  
I‚Äôm looking for love that makes life worth living all over again.
It is said that Zeus knew humans would be too powerful if we weren‚Äôt split at birth and condemned to search for our other half.  But really, he just meant us.  We‚Äôd be the power couple who saves the world.  Maybe we‚Äôve finally found each other, much to Zeus‚Äô chagrin?  If you think this might be the case, please dispatch a messenger to deliver your message to the following address at once.  We can then conduct a low-stakes holographic encounter through the aether  :)
TW2000X@GMAIL.COM
  More photos of me and my travels

Hey, thanks for stopping by! I‚Äôm Charlie, and I‚Äôm looking for a deep connection with a man, hopefully in the Bay Area, with an eye to finding my life partner. If you‚Äôre interested, please reach out! You can message me, get a mutual friend to intro us, email me, or use this link. 


About me
I come across as perceptive, caring, attuned, ambitious, and sincere. 
Here‚Äôs how some of my friends describe me:
Sasha Chapin: ‚ÄúI think of Charlie as a graceful mover, both in physical space and in conversational space ‚Äî he is a striking presence that improves the energy of a room.‚Äù
Catherio: ‚ÄúPerceptive, caring, attuned.‚Äù
Max Heitmann (ex-bf): ‚ÄúCharlie is his own person, probably the most himself of anyone I know. That person is sincere, curious, determined, and loving.‚Äù
Nora Ammann: ‚ÄúCharlie is thoughtful, caring and attuned, as well as spirited, curious and courageous. He is a good and loyal friend.‚Äù
John Salvatier: ‚ÄúUnrelentingly present.‚Äù
  

Relationship style
I lean monogamous, though I have a few years of experience with poly / open relationships, which I‚Äôm open to exploring with the right person. I think I‚Äôll want children in the future, but likely not within the next 5 years.
Interests
I spend a significant part of my life on self-discovery, introspecting, and deepening my relationships with others. I did some Serious Meditation a few years back, and had some profound experiences. I now spend a good chunk of my time on relational practices‚Äîwhich often looks like having very present, authentic, conversations. Relational practices bring more truth and love to my relationships and my self-expression, and nourish me massively. 
  

I like running events! I host dance parties and run regular relational practices; I‚Äôve run a Relateful (circling) immersion with Jordan Allen, a Coherence Psychology retreat with Malcolm Ocean, and many CFAR and CFAR-adjacent workshops. 
Besides that, I love to dance west coast swing (see me dancing here), lift heavy things with perfect form (see me lifting here), hang out with my friends‚Äô kids, and cry at Jacob Collier videos.
Career stuff: I‚Äôm Chief of Staff at Palisade Research, where we‚Äôre trying to build awareness of AI risks among policymakers. Previously, I worked as an instructor for the Center For Applied Rationality. And before that, I did a master‚Äôs at Oxford, and developed Bayesian ML models to estimate the effectiveness of interventions against COVID. Tyler Cowen described my paper as ‚ÄòThe best mask-wearing study so far?‚Äô.
  

About you
I‚Äôm usually more attracted to people who are more:
* Emotionally attuned: You‚Äôre in touch with yourself and listen deeply to others. You care a lot about communicating authentically.
* Vibrantly interested in stuff: You‚Äôre intellectually lively, sharp/analytical, and curious. 
* Extroverted / energetic.
* Playful!
* Grounded: You‚Äôre steady in yourself, and in touch with your masculine energy.
* Cute / sweet.
About us
Spending time with each other nourishes us, brings us closer to ourselves, and reminds us what life is about. 
I‚Äôd be especially happy if our relationship had:
* Deep listening. Over time, we come to know each other, and how we relate to one another, more and more deeply. 
* Alive, attuned, and perhaps wildly kinky, sex (I‚Äôm switch). Also, attuned touch; cuddling.
* We‚Äôre entangled with what matters most to each of us. We mutually support each other‚Äôs interests, and sometimes even participate / collaborate / build together.
* Fun: We go on adventures, nature or otherwise. We share music. We dance together, messy and silly, gentle and sensual. We play. We laugh lots. We cuddle up with an excellent movie or a trashy TV show.
If you‚Äôre interested, please reach out! You can message me, get a mutual friend to intro us, email me, or use this link.

Hi, I‚Äôm Nadia, 29, seeking the right partner for an altruistic power couple. Get in touch with me or share with men who you think might be a good match.
I work in a big consulting firm (for skill building and ‚Äúearning to give‚Äù) but previously dabbled in pandemic preparedness policy, research, nonprofit work, and a biotech startup. Located in Berlin as of August 2025.


  

This is the most recent picture (July 2025). I need to update my photos however, I have since cut my hair to shoulder length
üç¶Pro
* Energetic and bubbly. I laugh a lot, and I‚Äôm an easy audience if you want to test your own comedic aptitude. Examples of this:
   * Exercise and humour are my favourite coping skills, so‚Ä¶‚Äîwell, I better be strong and hilarious.
   * I play improv and host improv workshops sometimes.
   * I go hoarse before I run out of social energy.
* Deliberate approach to life, love efficiency, agentic as fuck.
   * Nothing that can‚Äôt be solved with a spreadsheet, a rubber duck, and coffee.
   * I found my last longterm partner after less than 2 months of building a funnel with screening criteria and setting up 5-min video calls. I won‚Äôt be a great match for most, and want to be mindful of everyone‚Äôs time while I find the person who is. 
* Excitable & curious. 
   * I‚Äôve been told that my questions are unique and inspiring.
   * I can make surface-level boring topics like patent landscaping and ISO standards sexy.
* Committed to self-improvement.
   * I had a lot of coaching and have set up systems so I don‚Äôt make the same mistake twice. I like having essentialist routines and hacking my brain.
   * I worked as a junior psychiatrist before. I am trained in CBT and NVC, and not afraid to use both to help us grow.
* Emotionally stable & pragmatic.
   * Friends appreciate how I balance succinctness and solution-focus with warmth and care.
   * For years, I lived out of a suitcase and didn‚Äôt really have a home address. I also cached in dozens of rejections before finding my academic supervisor‚Äîbut I‚Äôm really happy most of the time. This is to say, I‚Äôm rather tolerant of uncertainty and rejection in both my personal and professional life.
‚öñÔ∏è Neutral (?)
* Vegetarian.
   * It‚Äôs important to me that my partner is vegetarian or vegan, too.
* I don‚Äôt do alcohol, cigarettes, or THC.
   * I care about sharing an evidence-based, healthy lifestyle that acknowledges tradeoffs quantitatively.
   * Not all drugs are created equal; I‚Äôve found psychonauting with loved ones meaningful and connecting. 
* No children, by default.
   * Unlikely circumstances such as ¬≤‚Å¥‚ÅÑ‚Çá nanny support, a surrogate, and strong impact-related arguments could change my mind if my partner became very excited about having children.
* Good dancer.
   * As a pretty low priority, I would love to find someone who‚Äôs into dancing, too. But I‚Äôm too impatient to take beginner‚Äôs classes together. 
ü¶Ñ Con/‚ÄùNiche taste‚Äù
* I work a lot.
